    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "If you do it through a bash script, then it runs in a separate instance of Python, and the variables are lost when it finishes.\r\n\r\nIf you want to see the variables, you need to use the `%run` magic in IPython to run it in the same Python interpreter. If you want to avoid typing, you can use IPython's history to find the command again, or make it a macro with `%macro`."
  },
