    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "To rephrase what Thomas said, @rvadaga you should be able to do this from inside IPython.\r\n\r\nI wrote a simple `foo.py`:\r\n```python\r\nimport sys\r\nprint(sys.argv)\r\nx = len(sys.argv)\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd then I run it from IPython:\r\n```\r\nIn [1]: %run foo.py\r\n['foo.py']\r\n\r\nIn [2]: %run foo.py --hello there\r\n['foo.py', '--hello', 'there']\r\n\r\nIn [3]: x\r\nOut[3]: 3\r\n```"
  }
